This paper discusses a system for sharing privacy-sensitive datasets with strong privacy protections, which suggests that it could fit into several sub-categories related to privacy and data management. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on differential privacy and protecting sensitive data. cs.DB (Databases) is also a strong possibility, as the paper discusses data sharing and management. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another potential category, as the paper mentions using machine learning techniques to analyze the shared datasets. cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible categories, as the paper discusses the potential benefits of sharing data for social science research.
